      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "Hard to knock the form of KENNYS SON (10) since arriving in Victoria, making it three wins and a placing in four starts for Brent Lilley when he led and kept going to score by 4m at Kilmore last week. Draws on the back row this time but performed well from there three back at this venue. COLTRANE (11) kept his manners in check when scoring from this barrier two back at Ballarat before breaking when fourth here last time. Manners are a worry but he is good enough if he gets it right. VOLDAGHA (4) rises in grade but comes off a second-up win at Shepparton and has upside. AHUNDREDPLUS (8) could be close to a win after finishing second in her last three outings, the latest from this barrier at Kilmore.",
